Fair, but I wonder if you could achieve more control over the torment side of things. I eat out, hit most of my goals, and don’t torment myself. Maybe I set smaller goals though? If I was bodybuilding I couldn’t eat out. But lots of eating disorders are called bodybuilding.

I think you and I are generally agreed, but I do think it’s possible to eat out and still be healthy and hit goals. The problem with saying it “doesn’t work” is that many people will resign their goals after eating out a lot, often because it’s out of their control.

I eat out probably ~0 meals a week, but I don’t think it’s net worse. I don’t get baked good, I order salads/vegetable dishes with lots of grilled chicken, and add pretty conservative guesses for dressings/sauces. + for things like butter. It can definitely be done IMO

Living in the west village and maintaining a social life (friends and dating) makes cooking every meal pretty impractical, unfortunately. I do think it’s okay to eat out, you just have to control yourself and think about inputs

Lastly, and this was the biggest issue: anything that I couldn’t weigh or find on my MFP became a guilty pleasure. Eating out with friends? A cocktail w/ unknown proportions on a date? Suddenly I was always worried about / obsessing over food. My diet improved, but at what cost?
